 THE sum of N1million is at stake for the winner of the maiden Ken Saro Wiwa National Merit Award soccer tournament starting on Saturday, November 21, 2020. The football fiesta featuring 16 U 16 teams is put together C and G Sports Consultants to mark the 25th anniversary of the late author and environmentalist Ken Saro-Wiwa. Comrade Matthew Dighi, youth leader of the National Youth Council of the Ogoni people disclosed that the money will be shared by the three teams; N500, 000, N3000, 000 and N200, 000 respectively. He said the tournament billed to hold at the Ken Saro-Wiwa Polytechnic, will promote friendship and inspire youths in Ogoni and other Niger Delta communities. Outstanding players will also be selected for the establishment of the Ken Saro-Wiwa Football Academy. Director of C and G sports Onoviode Omagufi disclosed plans to select 22 best players for football trials in Europe with the intent of securing better future for youths in the oil producing Ogoni land and Niger Delta states.